94int journal_file_tail_end_by_pread(JournalFile *f, uint64_t *ret_offset) {
95        uint64_t p;
96        int r;
97
98        assert(f);
99        assert(f->header);
100        assert(ret_offset);
101
102        /* Same as journal_file_tail_end_by_mmap() below, but operates with pread() to avoid the mmap cache
103         * (and thus is thread safe) */
104
105        p = le64toh(f->header->tail_object_offset);
106        if (p == 0)
107                p = le64toh(f->header->header_size);
108        else {
109                Object tail;
110                uint64_t sz;
111
112                r = journal_file_read_object_header(f, OBJECT_UNUSED, p, &tail);
113                if (r < 0)
114                        return r;
115
116                sz = le64toh(tail.object.size);
117                if (sz > UINT64_MAX - sizeof(uint64_t) + 1)
118                        return -EBADMSG;
119
120                sz = ALIGN64(sz);
121                if (p > UINT64_MAX - sz)
122                        return -EBADMSG;
123
124                p += sz;
125        }
126
127        *ret_offset = p;
128
129        return 0;
130}

132int journal_file_tail_end_by_mmap(JournalFile *f, uint64_t *ret_offset) {
133        uint64_t p;
134        int r;
135
136        assert(f);
137        assert(f->header);
138        assert(ret_offset);
139
140        /* Same as journal_file_tail_end_by_pread() above, but operates with the usual mmap logic */
141
142        p = le64toh(f->header->tail_object_offset);
143        if (p == 0)
144                p = le64toh(f->header->header_size);
145        else {
146                Object *tail;
147                uint64_t sz;
148
149                r = journal_file_move_to_object(f, OBJECT_UNUSED, p, &tail);
150                if (r < 0)

159                        return -EBADMSG;
160
161                p += sz;
162        }
163
164        *ret_offset = p;
165
166        return 0;

169int journal_file_set_offline_thread_join(JournalFile *f) {
170        int r;
171
172        assert(f);
173
174        if (f->offline_state == OFFLINE_JOINED)
175                return 0;
176
177        r = pthread_join(f->offline_thread, NULL);
178        if (r)
179                return -r;
180
181        f->offline_state = OFFLINE_JOINED;
182
183        if (mmap_cache_fd_got_sigbus(f->cache_fd))
184                return -EIO;
185
186        return 0;
187}

189static int journal_file_set_online(JournalFile *f) {
190        bool wait = true;
191
192        assert(f);
193
194        if (!journal_file_writable(f))
195                return -EPERM;
196
197        if (f->fd < 0 || !f->header)
198                return -EINVAL;
199
200        while (wait) {
201                switch (f->offline_state) {
202                case OFFLINE_JOINED:
203                        /* No offline thread, no need to wait. */
204                        wait = false;
205                        break;
206
207                case OFFLINE_SYNCING: {
208                                OfflineState tmp_state = OFFLINE_SYNCING;
209                                if (!__atomic_compare_exchange_n(&f->offline_state, &tmp_state, OFFLINE_CANCEL,
210                                    false, __ATOMIC_SEQ_CST, __ATOMIC_SEQ_CST))
211                                        continue;
212                        }
213                        /* Canceled syncing prior to offlining, no need to wait. */
214                        wait = false;
215                        break;
216
217                case OFFLINE_AGAIN_FROM_SYNCING: {
218                                OfflineState tmp_state = OFFLINE_AGAIN_FROM_SYNCING;
219                                if (!__atomic_compare_exchange_n(&f->offline_state, &tmp_state, OFFLINE_CANCEL,
220                                    false, __ATOMIC_SEQ_CST, __ATOMIC_SEQ_CST))
221                                        continue;
222                        }
223                        /* Canceled restart from syncing, no need to wait. */
224                        wait = false;
225                        break;
226
227                case OFFLINE_AGAIN_FROM_OFFLINING: {
228                                OfflineState tmp_state = OFFLINE_AGAIN_FROM_OFFLINING;
229                                if (!__atomic_compare_exchange_n(&f->offline_state, &tmp_state, OFFLINE_CANCEL,
230                                    false, __ATOMIC_SEQ_CST, __ATOMIC_SEQ_CST))
231                                        continue;
232                        }
233                        /* Canceled restart from offlining, must wait for offlining to complete however. */
234                        _fallthrough_;
235                default: {
236                        int r;
237
238                        r = journal_file_set_offline_thread_join(f);
239                        if (r < 0)
240                                return r;
241
242                        wait = false;
243                        break;
244                }
245                }
246        }
247
248        if (mmap_cache_fd_got_sigbus(f->cache_fd))
249                return -EIO;
250
251        switch (f->header->state) {
252                case STATE_ONLINE:
253                        return 0;
254
255                case STATE_OFFLINE:
256                        f->header->state = STATE_ONLINE;
257                        (void) fsync(f->fd);
258                        return 0;
259
260                default:
261                        return -EINVAL;
262        }
263}

265JournalFile* journal_file_close(JournalFile *f) {
266        if (!f)
267                return NULL;
268
269        if (f->cache_fd)
270                mmap_cache_fd_free(f->cache_fd);
271
272        if (f->close_fd)
273                safe_close(f->fd);
274        free(f->path);
275
276        ordered_hashmap_free_free(f->chain_cache);
277
278#if HAVE_COMPRESSION
279        free(f->compress_buffer);
280#endif
281
282#if HAVE_GCRYPT
283        if (f->fss_file)
284                munmap(f->fss_file, PAGE_ALIGN(f->fss_file_size));
285        else
286                free(f->fsprg_state);
287
288        free(f->fsprg_seed);
289
290        if (f->hmac)
291                gcry_md_close(f->hmac);
292#endif
293
294        return mfree(f);
295}

297static int journal_file_init_header(JournalFile *f, JournalFileFlags file_flags, JournalFile *template) {
298        Header h = {};
299        ssize_t k;
300        bool keyed_hash, seal = false;
301        int r;
302
303        assert(f);
304
305        /* We turn on keyed hashes by default, but provide an environment variable to turn them off, if
306         * people really want that */
307        r = getenv_bool("SYSTEMD_JOURNAL_KEYED_HASH");
308        if (r < 0) {
309                if (r != -ENXIO)
310                        log_debug_errno(r, "Failed to parse $SYSTEMD_JOURNAL_KEYED_HASH environment variable, ignoring: %m");
311                keyed_hash = true;
312        } else
313                keyed_hash = r;
314
315#if HAVE_GCRYPT
316        /* Try to load the FSPRG state, and if we can't, then just don't do sealing */
317        seal = FLAGS_SET(file_flags, JOURNAL_SEAL) && journal_file_fss_load(f) >= 0;
318#endif
319
320        memcpy(h.signature, HEADER_SIGNATURE, 8);
321        h.header_size = htole64(ALIGN64(sizeof(h)));
322
323        h.incompatible_flags |= htole32(
324                        FLAGS_SET(file_flags, JOURNAL_COMPRESS) *
325                        COMPRESSION_TO_HEADER_INCOMPATIBLE_FLAG(DEFAULT_COMPRESSION) |
326                        keyed_hash * HEADER_INCOMPATIBLE_KEYED_HASH);
327
328        h.compatible_flags = htole32(seal * HEADER_COMPATIBLE_SEALED);
329
330        r = sd_id128_randomize(&h.file_id);
331        if (r < 0)
332                return r;
333
334        if (template) {
335                h.seqnum_id = template->header->seqnum_id;
336                h.tail_entry_seqnum = template->header->tail_entry_seqnum;
337        } else
338                h.seqnum_id = h.file_id;
339
340        k = pwrite(f->fd, &h, sizeof(h), 0);
341        if (k < 0)
342                return -errno;
343
344        if (k != sizeof(h))
345                return -EIO;
346
347        return 0;
348}

350static int journal_file_refresh_header(JournalFile *f) {
351        int r;
352
353        assert(f);
354        assert(f->header);
355
356        r = sd_id128_get_machine(&f->header->machine_id);
357        if (IN_SET(r, -ENOENT, -ENOMEDIUM))
358                /* We don't have a machine-id, let's continue without */
359                zero(f->header->machine_id);
360        else if (r < 0)
361                return r;
362
363        r = sd_id128_get_boot(&f->header->boot_id);
364        if (r < 0)
365                return r;
366
367        r = journal_file_set_online(f);
368
369        /* Sync the online state to disk; likely just created a new file, also sync the directory this file
370         * is located in. */
371        (void) fsync_full(f->fd);
372
373        return r;
374}

376static bool warn_wrong_flags(const JournalFile *f, bool compatible) {
377        const uint32_t any = compatible ? HEADER_COMPATIBLE_ANY : HEADER_INCOMPATIBLE_ANY,
378                supported = compatible ? HEADER_COMPATIBLE_SUPPORTED : HEADER_INCOMPATIBLE_SUPPORTED;
379        const char *type = compatible ? "compatible" : "incompatible";
380        uint32_t flags;
381
382        flags = le32toh(compatible ? f->header->compatible_flags : f->header->incompatible_flags);
383
384        if (flags & ~supported) {
385                if (flags & ~any)
386                        log_debug("Journal file %s has unknown %s flags 0x%"PRIx32,
387                                  f->path, type, flags & ~any);
388                flags = (flags & any) & ~supported;
389                if (flags) {
390                        const char* strv[5];
391                        size_t n = 0;
392                        _cleanup_free_ char *t = NULL;
393
394                        if (compatible) {
395                                if (flags & HEADER_COMPATIBLE_SEALED)
396                                        strv[n++] = "sealed";
397                        } else {
398                                if (flags & HEADER_INCOMPATIBLE_COMPRESSED_XZ)
399                                        strv[n++] = "xz-compressed";
400                                if (flags & HEADER_INCOMPATIBLE_COMPRESSED_LZ4)
401                                        strv[n++] = "lz4-compressed";
402                                if (flags & HEADER_INCOMPATIBLE_COMPRESSED_ZSTD)
403                                        strv[n++] = "zstd-compressed";
404                                if (flags & HEADER_INCOMPATIBLE_KEYED_HASH)
405                                        strv[n++] = "keyed-hash";
406                        }
407                        strv[n] = NULL;
408                        assert(n < ELEMENTSOF(strv));
409
410                        t = strv_join((char**) strv, ", ");
411                        log_debug("Journal file %s uses %s %s %s disabled at compilation time.",
412                                  f->path, type, n > 1 ? "flags" : "flag", strnull(t));
413                }
414                return true;
415        }
416
417        return false;
418}

420static int journal_file_verify_header(JournalFile *f) {
421        uint64_t arena_size, header_size;
422
423        assert(f);
424        assert(f->header);
425
426        if (memcmp(f->header->signature, HEADER_SIGNATURE, 8))
427                return -EBADMSG;
428
429        /* In both read and write mode we refuse to open files with incompatible
430         * flags we don't know. */
431        if (warn_wrong_flags(f, false))
432                return -EPROTONOSUPPORT;
433
434        /* When open for writing we refuse to open files with compatible flags, too. */
435        if (journal_file_writable(f) && warn_wrong_flags(f, true))
436                return -EPROTONOSUPPORT;
437
438        if (f->header->state >= _STATE_MAX)
439                return -EBADMSG;
440
441        header_size = le64toh(READ_NOW(f->header->header_size));
442
443        /* The first addition was n_data, so check that we are at least this large */
444        if (header_size < HEADER_SIZE_MIN)
445                return -EBADMSG;
446
447        if (JOURNAL_HEADER_SEALED(f->header) && !JOURNAL_HEADER_CONTAINS(f->header, n_entry_arrays))
448                return -EBADMSG;
449
450        arena_size = le64toh(READ_NOW(f->header->arena_size));
451
452        if (
 Recommendations (Experimental)  R1: (123 <= header_size + arena_size && header_size + arena_size < f && 123 <= last_stat + st_size && last_stat + st_size < uint64_t)
R2: (123 * (header_size + arena_size) + f * (last_stat + st_size) + st_size - 123)
R3: (123 <= header_size + arena_size && header_size + arena_size < f.last_stat && 123 <= st_size + uint64_t && st_size + uint64_t < f.xx_g)
R4: (123 > (header_size + arena_size) || (header_size + arena_size) >= f.last_stat)
R5: (123 <= header_size && arena_size * f <= header_size * last_stat && header_size * header_size >= st_size * arena_size)
 Score  Issue:  1 unfamiliar pattern(s) detected 
Cost: 15.95, Total Score: 1015.95
Class: complex_2
UINT64_MAX - header_size < arena_size || header_size + arena_size > (uint64_t) f->last_stat.st_size)
453                return -ENODATA;
454
455        if (le64toh(f->header->tail_object_offset) > header_size + arena_size)
456                return -ENODATA;
457
458        if (!VALID64(le64toh(f->header->data_hash_table_offset)) ||
459            !VALID64(le64toh(f->header->field_hash_table_offset)) ||
460            !VALID64(le64toh(f->header->tail_object_offset)) ||
461            !VALID64(le64toh(f->header->entry_array_offset)))
462                return -ENODATA;
463
464        if (journal_file_writable(f)) {
465                sd_id128_t machine_id;
466                uint8_t state;
467                int r;
468
469                r = sd_id128_get_machine(&machine_id);
470                if (r < 0)
471                        return r;
472
473                if (!sd_id128_equal(machine_id, f->header->machine_id))
474                        return -EHOSTDOWN;
475
476                state = f->header->state;
477
478                if (state == STATE_ARCHIVED)
479                        return -ESHUTDOWN; /* Already archived */
480                else if (state == STATE_ONLINE)
481                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBUSY),
482                                               "Journal file %s is already online. Assuming unclean closing.",
483                                               f->path);
484                else if (state != STATE_OFFLINE)
485                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBUSY),
486                                               "Journal file %s has unknown state %i.",
487                                               f->path, state);
488
489                if (f->header->field_hash_table_size == 0 || f->header->data_hash_table_size == 0)
490                        return -EBADMSG;
491
492                /* Don't permit appending to files from the future. Because otherwise the realtime timestamps wouldn't
493                 * be strictly ordered in the entries in the file anymore, and we can't have that since it breaks
494                 * bisection. */
495                if (le64toh(f->header->tail_entry_realtime) > now(CLOCK_REALTIME))
496                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(ETXTBSY),
497                                               "Journal file %s is from the future, refusing to append new data to it that'd be older.",
498                                               f->path);
499        }
500
501        return 0;
502}
503
504int journal_file_fstat(JournalFile *f) {
505        int r;
506
507        assert(f);
508        assert(f->fd >= 0);
509
510        if (fstat(f->fd, &f->last_stat) < 0)
511                return -errno;
512
513        f->last_stat_usec = now(CLOCK_MONOTONIC);
514
515        /* Refuse dealing with files that aren't regular */
516        r = stat_verify_regular(&f->last_stat);
517        if (r < 0)
518                return r;
519
520        /* Refuse appending to files that are already deleted */
521        if (f->last_stat.st_nlink <= 0)
522                return -EIDRM;
523
524        return 0;
525}
526
527static int journal_file_allocate(JournalFile *f, uint64_t offset, uint64_t size) {
528        uint64_t old_size, new_size, old_header_size, old_arena_size;
529        int r;
530
531        assert(f);
532        assert(f->header);
533
534        /* We assume that this file is not sparse, and we know that for sure, since we always call
535         * posix_fallocate() ourselves */
536
537        if (size > PAGE_ALIGN_DOWN(UINT64_MAX) - offset)
538                return -EINVAL;
539
540        if (mmap_cache_fd_got_sigbus(f->cache_fd))
541                return -EIO;
542
543        old_header_size = le64toh(READ_NOW(f->header->header_size));
544        old_arena_size = le64toh(READ_NOW(f->header->arena_size));
545        if (old_arena_size > PAGE_ALIGN_DOWN(UINT64_MAX) - old_header_size)
546                return -EBADMSG;
547
548        old_size = old_header_size + old_arena_size;
549
550        new_size = MAX(PAGE_ALIGN(offset + size), old_header_size);
551
552        if (new_size <= old_size) {
553
554                /* We already pre-allocated enough space, but before
555                 * we write to it, let's check with fstat() if the
556                 * file got deleted, in order make sure we don't throw
557                 * away the data immediately. Don't check fstat() for
558                 * all writes though, but only once ever 10s. */
559
560                if (f->last_stat_usec + LAST_STAT_REFRESH_USEC > now(CLOCK_MONOTONIC))
561                        return 0;
562
563                return journal_file_fstat(f);
564        }
565
566        /* Allocate more space. */
567
568        if (f->metrics.max_size > 0 && new_size > f->metrics.max_size)
569                return -E2BIG;
570
571        if (new_size > f->metrics.min_size && f->metrics.keep_free > 0) {
572                struct statvfs svfs;
573
574                if (fstatvfs(f->fd, &svfs) >= 0) {
575                        uint64_t available;
576
577                        available = LESS_BY((uint64_t) svfs.f_bfree * (uint64_t) svfs.f_bsize, f->metrics.keep_free);
578
579                        if (new_size - old_size > available)
580                                return -E2BIG;
581                }
582        }
583
584        /* Increase by larger blocks at once */
585        new_size = DIV_ROUND_UP(new_size, FILE_SIZE_INCREASE) * FILE_SIZE_INCREASE;
586        if (f->metrics.max_size > 0 && new_size > f->metrics.max_size)
587                new_size = f->metrics.max_size;
588
589        /* Note that the glibc fallocate() fallback is very
590           inefficient, hence we try to minimize the allocation area
591           as we can. */
592        r = posix_fallocate_loop(f->fd, old_size, new_size - old_size);
593        if (r < 0)
594                return r;
595
596        f->header->arena_size = htole64(new_size - old_header_size);
597
598        return journal_file_fstat(f);
599}
600
601static unsigned type_to_context(ObjectType type) {
602        /* One context for each type, plus one catch-all for the rest */
603        assert_cc(_OBJECT_TYPE_MAX <= MMAP_CACHE_MAX_CONTEXTS);
604        assert_cc(CONTEXT_HEADER < MMAP_CACHE_MAX_CONTEXTS);
605        return type > OBJECT_UNUSED && type < _OBJECT_TYPE_MAX ? type : 0;
606}
607
608static int journal_file_move_to(
609                JournalFile *f,
610                ObjectType type,
611                bool keep_always,
612                uint64_t offset,
613                uint64_t size,
614                void **ret) {
615
616        int r;
617
618        assert(f);
619        assert(ret);
620
621        if (size <= 0)
622                return -EINVAL;
623
624        if (size > UINT64_MAX - offset)
625                return -EBADMSG;
626
627        /* Avoid SIGBUS on invalid accesses */
628        if (offset + size > (uint64_t) f->last_stat.st_size) {
629                /* Hmm, out of range? Let's refresh the fstat() data
630                 * first, before we trust that check. */
631
632                r = journal_file_fstat(f);
633                if (r < 0)
634                        return r;
635
636                if (offset + size > (uint64_t) f->last_stat.st_size)
637                        return -EADDRNOTAVAIL;
638        }
639
640        return mmap_cache_fd_get(f->cache_fd, type_to_context(type), keep_always, offset, size, &f->last_stat, ret);
641}
642
643static uint64_t minimum_header_size(Object *o) {
644
645        static const uint64_t table[] = {
646                [OBJECT_DATA]             = sizeof(DataObject),
647                [OBJECT_FIELD]            = sizeof(FieldObject),
648                [OBJECT_ENTRY]            = sizeof(EntryObject),
649                [OBJECT_DATA_HASH_TABLE]  = sizeof(HashTableObject),
650                [OBJECT_FIELD_HASH_TABLE] = sizeof(HashTableObject),
651                [OBJECT_ENTRY_ARRAY]      = sizeof(EntryArrayObject),
652                [OBJECT_TAG]              = sizeof(TagObject),
653        };
654
655        if (o->object.type >= ELEMENTSOF(table) || table[o->object.type] <= 0)
656                return sizeof(ObjectHeader);
657
658        return table[o->object.type];
659}
660
661static int check_object_header(Object *o, ObjectType type, uint64_t offset) {
662        uint64_t s;
663
664        assert(o);
665
666        s = le64toh(READ_NOW(o->object.size));
667        if (s == 0)
668                return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
669                                       "Attempt to move to uninitialized object: %" PRIu64,
670                                       offset);
671
672        if (s < sizeof(ObjectHeader))
673                return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
674                                       "Attempt to move to overly short object: %" PRIu64,
675                                       offset);
676
677        if (o->object.type <= OBJECT_UNUSED)
678                return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
679                                       "Attempt to move to object with invalid type: %" PRIu64,
680                                       offset);
681
682        if (
 Recommendations (Experimental)  R1: (type > 123 && o != type)
R2: ((type > 123) && (o != type))
R3: (type > 123 && o->object != type)
R4: (type > 123 && o.object != type)
R5: (type > 123 && o->type != type)
 Score  Issue:  1 unfamiliar pattern(s) detected 
Cost: 12.75, Total Score: 1012.75
Class: complex_2
type > OBJECT_UNUSED && o->object.type != type)
683                return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
684                                       "Attempt to move to object of unexpected type: %" PRIu64,
685                                       offset);
686
687        if (s < minimum_header_size(o))
688                return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
689                                       "Attempt to move to truncated object: %" PRIu64,
690                                       offset);
691
692        return 0;
693}
694
695/* Lightweight object checks. We want this to be fast, so that we won't
696 * slowdown every journal_file_move_to_object() call too much. */
697static int check_object(Object *o, uint64_t offset) {
698        assert(o);
699
700        switch (o->object.type) {
701
702        case OBJECT_DATA:
703                if ((le64toh(o->data.entry_offset) == 0) ^ (le64toh(o->data.n_entries) == 0))
704                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
705                                               "Bad n_entries: %" PRIu64 ": %" PRIu64,
706                                               le64toh(o->data.n_entries),
707                                               offset);
708
709                if (le64toh(o->object.size) <= offsetof(Object, data.payload))
710                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
711                                               "Bad object size (<= %zu): %" PRIu64 ": %" PRIu64,
712                                               offsetof(Object, data.payload),
713                                               le64toh(o->object.size),
714                                               offset);
715
716                if (!VALID64(le64toh(o->data.next_hash_offset)) ||
717                    !VALID64(le64toh(o->data.next_field_offset)) ||
718                    !VALID64(le64toh(o->data.entry_offset)) ||
719                    !VALID64(le64toh(o->data.entry_array_offset)))
720                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
721                                               "Invalid offset, next_hash_offset=" OFSfmt ", next_field_offset=" OFSfmt ", entry_offset=" OFSfmt ", entry_array_offset=" OFSfmt ": %" PRIu64,
722                                               le64toh(o->data.next_hash_offset),
723                                               le64toh(o->data.next_field_offset),
724                                               le64toh(o->data.entry_offset),
725                                               le64toh(o->data.entry_array_offset),
726                                               offset);
727
728                break;
729
730        case OBJECT_FIELD:
731                if (le64toh(o->object.size) <= offsetof(Object, field.payload))
732                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
733                                               "Bad field size (<= %zu): %" PRIu64 ": %" PRIu64,
734                                               offsetof(Object, field.payload),
735                                               le64toh(o->object.size),
736                                               offset);
737
738                if (!VALID64(le64toh(o->field.next_hash_offset)) ||
739                    !VALID64(le64toh(o->field.head_data_offset)))
740                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
741                                               "Invalid offset, next_hash_offset=" OFSfmt ", head_data_offset=" OFSfmt ": %" PRIu64,
742                                               le64toh(o->field.next_hash_offset),
743                                               le64toh(o->field.head_data_offset),
744                                               offset);
745                break;
746
747        case OBJECT_ENTRY: {
748                uint64_t sz;
749
750                sz = le64toh(READ_NOW(o->object.size));
751                if (sz < offsetof(Object, entry.items) ||
752                    (sz - offsetof(Object, entry.items)) % sizeof(EntryItem) != 0)
753                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
754                                               "Bad entry size (<= %zu): %" PRIu64 ": %" PRIu64,
755                                               offsetof(Object, entry.items),
756                                               sz,
757                                               offset);
758
759                if ((sz - offsetof(Object, entry.items)) / sizeof(EntryItem) <= 0)
760                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
761                                               "Invalid number items in entry: %" PRIu64 ": %" PRIu64,
762                                               (sz - offsetof(Object, entry.items)) / sizeof(EntryItem),
763                                               offset);
764
765                if (le64toh(o->entry.seqnum) <= 0)
766                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
767                                               "Invalid entry seqnum: %" PRIx64 ": %" PRIu64,
768                                               le64toh(o->entry.seqnum),
769                                               offset);
770
771                if (!VALID_REALTIME(le64toh(o->entry.realtime)))
772                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
773                                               "Invalid entry realtime timestamp: %" PRIu64 ": %" PRIu64,
774                                               le64toh(o->entry.realtime),
775                                               offset);
776
777                if (!VALID_MONOTONIC(le64toh(o->entry.monotonic)))
778                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
779                                               "Invalid entry monotonic timestamp: %" PRIu64 ": %" PRIu64,
780                                               le64toh(o->entry.monotonic),
781                                               offset);
782
783                break;
784        }
785
786        case OBJECT_DATA_HASH_TABLE:
787        case OBJECT_FIELD_HASH_TABLE: {
788                uint64_t sz;
789
790                sz = le64toh(READ_NOW(o->object.size));
791                if (sz < offsetof(Object, hash_table.items) ||
792                    (sz - offsetof(Object, hash_table.items)) % sizeof(HashItem) != 0 ||
793                    (sz - offsetof(Object, hash_table.items)) / sizeof(HashItem) <= 0)
794                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
795                                               "Invalid %s hash table size: %" PRIu64 ": %" PRIu64,
796                                               o->object.type == OBJECT_DATA_HASH_TABLE ? "data" : "field",
797                                               sz,
798                                               offset);
799
800                break;
801        }
802
803        case OBJECT_ENTRY_ARRAY: {
804                uint64_t sz;
805
806                sz = le64toh(READ_NOW(o->object.size));
807                if (sz < offsetof(Object, entry_array.items) ||
808                    (sz - offsetof(Object, entry_array.items)) % sizeof(le64_t) != 0 ||
809                    (sz - offsetof(Object, entry_array.items)) / sizeof(le64_t) <= 0)
810                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
811                                               "Invalid object entry array size: %" PRIu64 ": %" PRIu64,
812                                               sz,
813                                               offset);
814
815                if (!VALID64(le64toh(o->entry_array.next_entry_array_offset)))
816                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
817                                               "Invalid object entry array next_entry_array_offset: " OFSfmt ": %" PRIu64,
818                                               le64toh(o->entry_array.next_entry_array_offset),
819                                               offset);
820
821                break;
822        }
823
824        case OBJECT_TAG:
825                if (le64toh(o->object.size) != sizeof(TagObject))
826                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
827                                               "Invalid object tag size: %" PRIu64 ": %" PRIu64,
828                                               le64toh(o->object.size),
829                                               offset);
830
831                if (!VALID_EPOCH(le64toh(o->tag.epoch)))
832                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
833                                               "Invalid object tag epoch: %" PRIu64 ": %" PRIu64,
834                                               le64toh(o->tag.epoch), offset);
835
836                break;
837        }
838
839        return 0;
840}
841
842int journal_file_move_to_object(JournalFile *f, ObjectType type, uint64_t offset, Object **ret) {
843        int r;
844        Object *o;
845
846        assert(f);
847
848        /* Objects may only be located at multiple of 64 bit */
849        if (!VALID64(offset))
850                return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
851                                       "Attempt to move to object at non-64bit boundary: %" PRIu64,
852                                       offset);
853
854        /* Object may not be located in the file header */
855        if (offset < le64toh(f->header->header_size))
856                return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
857                                       "Attempt to move to object located in file header: %" PRIu64,
858                                       offset);
859
860        r = journal_file_move_to(f, type, false, offset, sizeof(ObjectHeader), (void**) &o);
861        if (r < 0)
862                return r;
863
864        r = check_object_header(o, type, offset);
865        if (r < 0)
866                return r;
867
868        r = journal_file_move_to(f, type, false, offset, le64toh(READ_NOW(o->object.size)), (void**) &o);
869        if (r < 0)
870                return r;
871
872        r = check_object_header(o, type, offset);
873        if (r < 0)
874                return r;
875
876        r = check_object(o, offset);
877        if (r < 0)
878                return r;
879
880        if (ret)
881                *ret = o;
882
883        return 0;
884}
885
886int journal_file_read_object_header(JournalFile *f, ObjectType type, uint64_t offset, Object *ret) {
887        ssize_t n;
888        Object o;
889        int r;
890
891        assert(f);
892
893        /* Objects may only be located at multiple of 64 bit */
894        if (!VALID64(offset))
895                return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
896                                       "Attempt to read object at non-64bit boundary: %" PRIu64,
897                                       offset);
898
899        /* Object may not be located in the file header */
900        if (offset < le64toh(f->header->header_size))
901                return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
902                                       "Attempt to read object located in file header: %" PRIu64,
903                                       offset);
904
905        /* This will likely read too much data but it avoids having to call pread() twice. */
906        n = pread(f->fd, &o, sizeof(o), offset);
907        if (n < 0)
908                return log_debug_errno(errno, "Failed to read journal file at offset: %" PRIu64,
909                                       offset);
910
911        if ((size_t) n < sizeof(o.object))
912                return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EIO),
913                                       "Failed to read short object at offset: %" PRIu64,
914                                       offset);
915
916        r = check_object_header(&o, type, offset);
917        if (r < 0)
918                return r;
919
920        if ((size_t) n < minimum_header_size(&o))
921                return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EIO),
922                                       "Short read while reading object: %" PRIu64,
923                                       offset);
924
925        r = check_object(&o, offset);
926        if (r < 0)
927                return r;
928
929        if (ret)
930                *ret = o;
931
932        return 0;
933}
934
935static uint64_t journal_file_entry_seqnum(
936                JournalFile *f,
937                uint64_t *seqnum) {
938
939        uint64_t ret;
940
941        assert(f);
942        assert(f->header);
943
944        /* Picks a new sequence number for the entry we are about to add and returns it. */
945
946        ret = le64toh(f->header->tail_entry_seqnum) + 1;
947
948        if (seqnum) {
949                /* If an external seqnum counter was passed, we update both the local and the external one,
950                 * and set it to the maximum of both */
951
952                if (*seqnum + 1 > ret)
953                        ret = *seqnum + 1;
954
955                *seqnum = ret;
956        }
957
958        f->header->tail_entry_seqnum = htole64(ret);
959
960        if (f->header->head_entry_seqnum == 0)
961                f->header->head_entry_seqnum = htole64(ret);
962
963        return ret;
964}

966int journal_file_append_object(
967                JournalFile *f,
968                ObjectType type,
969                uint64_t size,
970                Object **ret,
971                uint64_t *ret_offset) {
972
973        int r;
974        uint64_t p;
975        Object *o;
976
977        assert(f);
978        assert(f->header);
979        assert(type > OBJECT_UNUSED && type < _OBJECT_TYPE_MAX);
980        assert(size >= sizeof(ObjectHeader));
981
982        r = journal_file_set_online(f);
983        if (r < 0)
984                return r;
985
986        r = journal_file_tail_end_by_mmap(f, &p);
987        if (r < 0)
988                return r;
989
990        r = journal_file_allocate(f, p, size);
991        if (r < 0)
992                return r;
993
994        r = journal_file_move_to(f, type, false, p, size, (void**) &o);
995        if (r < 0)
996                return r;
997
998        o->object = (ObjectHeader) {
999                .type = type,
1000                .size = htole64(size),
1001        };
1002
1003        f->header->tail_object_offset = htole64(p);
1004        f->header->n_objects = htole64(le64toh(f->header->n_objects) + 1);
1005
1006        if (ret)
1007                *ret = o;
1008
1009        if (ret_offset)
1010                *ret_offset = p;
1011
1012        return 0;
1013}

1015static int journal_file_setup_data_hash_table(JournalFile *f) {
1016        uint64_t s, p;
1017        Object *o;
1018        int r;
1019
1020        assert(f);
1021        assert(f->header);
1022
1023        /* We estimate that we need 1 hash table entry per 768 bytes
1024           of journal file and we want to make sure we never get
1025           beyond 75% fill level. Calculate the hash table size for
1026           the maximum file size based on these metrics. */
1027
1028        s = (f->metrics.max_size * 4 / 768 / 3) * sizeof(HashItem);
1029        if (s < DEFAULT_DATA_HASH_TABLE_SIZE)
1030                s = DEFAULT_DATA_HASH_TABLE_SIZE;
1031
1032        log_debug("Reserving %"PRIu64" entries in data hash table.", s / sizeof(HashItem));
1033
1034        r = journal_file_append_object(f,
1035                                       OBJECT_DATA_HASH_TABLE,
1036                                       offsetof(Object, hash_table.items) + s,
1037                                       &o, &p);
1038        if (r < 0)
1039                return r;
1040
1041        memzero(o->hash_table.items, s);
1042
1043        f->header->data_hash_table_offset = htole64(p + offsetof(Object, hash_table.items));
1044        f->header->data_hash_table_size = htole64(s);
1045
1046        return 0;
1047}

1130static int journal_file_link_field(
1131                JournalFile *f,
1132                Object *o,
1133                uint64_t offset,
1134                uint64_t hash) {
1135
1136        uint64_t p, h, m;
1137        int r;
1138
1139        assert(f);
1140        assert(f->header);
1141        assert(f->field_hash_table);
1142        assert(o);
1143        assert(offset > 0);
1144
1145        if (o->object.type != OBJECT_FIELD)
1146                return -EINVAL;
1147
1148        m = le64toh(READ_NOW(f->header->field_hash_table_size)) / sizeof(HashItem);
1149        if (m <= 0)
1150                return -EBADMSG;
1151
1152        /* This might alter the window we are looking at */
1153        o->field.next_hash_offset = o->field.head_data_offset = 0;
1154
1155        h = hash % m;
1156        p = le64toh(f->field_hash_table[h].tail_hash_offset);
1157        if (p == 0)
1158                f->field_hash_table[h].head_hash_offset = htole64(offset);
1159        else {
1160                r = journal_file_move_to_object(f, OBJECT_FIELD, p, &o);
1161                if (r < 0)
1162                        return r;
1163
1164                o->field.next_hash_offset = htole64(offset);
1165        }
1166
1167        f->field_hash_table[h].tail_hash_offset = htole64(offset);
1168
1169        if (JOURNAL_HEADER_CONTAINS(f->header, n_fields))
1170                f->header->n_fields = htole64(le64toh(f->header->n_fields) + 1);
1171
1172        return 0;

1175static int journal_file_link_data(
1176                JournalFile *f,
1177                Object *o,
1178                uint64_t offset,
1179                uint64_t hash) {
1180
1181        uint64_t p, h, m;
1182        int r;
1183
1184        assert(f);
1185        assert(f->header);
1186        assert(f->data_hash_table);
1187        assert(o);
1188        assert(offset > 0);

1199        o->data.entry_offset = o->data.entry_array_offset = 0;

1216        }

1219

1226static int next_hash_offset(
1227                JournalFile *f,
1228                uint64_t *p,
1229                le64_t *next_hash_offset,
1230                uint64_t *depth,
1231                le64_t *header_max_depth) {
1232
1233        uint64_t nextp;
1234
1235        nextp = le64toh(READ_NOW(*next_hash_offset));
1236        if (nextp > 0) {
1237                if (nextp <= *p) /* Refuse going in loops */
1238                        return log_debug_errno(SYNTHETIC_ERRNO(EBADMSG),
1239                                               "Detected hash item loop in %s, refusing.", f->path);
1240
1241                (*depth)++;
1242
1243                /* If the depth of this hash chain is larger than all others we have seen so far, record it */
1244                if (header_max_depth && journal_file_writable(f))
1245                        *header_max_depth = htole64(MAX(*depth, le64toh(*header_max_depth)));
1246        }
1247
1248        *p = nextp;
1249        return 0;
1250}

1252int journal_file_find_field_object_with_hash(
1253                JournalFile *f,
1254                const void *field, uint64_t size, uint64_t hash,
1255                Object **ret, uint64_t *ret_offset) {
1256
1257        uint64_t p, osize, h, m, depth = 0;
1258        int r;
1259
1260        assert(f);
1261        assert(f->header);
1262        assert(field && size > 0);
1263
1264        /* If the field hash table is empty, we can't find anything */
1265        if (le64toh(f->header->field_hash_table_size) <= 0)
1266                return 0;
1267
1268        /* Map the field hash table, if it isn't mapped yet. */
1269        r = journal_file_map_field_hash_table(f);
1270        if (r < 0)
1271                return r;
1272
1273        osize = offsetof(Object, field.payload) + size;
1274
1275        m = le64toh(READ_NOW(f->header->field_hash_table_size)) / sizeof(HashItem);
1276        if (m <= 0)
1277                return -EBADMSG;
1278
1279        h = hash % m;
1280        p = le64toh(f->field_hash_table[h].head_hash_offset);
1281        while (p > 0) {
1282                Object *o;
1283
1284                r = journal_file_move_to_object(f, OBJECT_FIELD, p, &o);
1285                if (r < 0)
1286                        return r;
1287
1288                if (le64toh(o->field.hash) == hash &&
1289                    le64toh(o->object.size) == osize &&
1290                    memcmp(o->field.payload, field, size) == 0) {
1291
1292                        if (ret)
1293                                *ret = o;
1294                        if (ret_offset)
1295                                *ret_offset = p;
1296
1297                        return 1;
1298                }
1299
1300                r = next_hash_offset(
1301                                f,
1302                                &p,
1303                                &o->field.next_hash_offset,
1304                                &depth,
1305                                JOURNAL_HEADER_CONTAINS(f->header, field_hash_chain_depth) ? &f->header->field_hash_chain_depth : NULL);
1306                if (r < 0)
1307                        return r;
1308        }
1309
1310        return 0;
1311}

1313uint64_t journal_file_hash_data(
1314                JournalFile *f,
1315                const void *data,
1316                size_t sz) {
1317
1318        assert(f);
1319        assert(data || sz == 0);
1320
1321        /* We try to unify our codebase on siphash, hence new-styled journal files utilizing the keyed hash
1322         * function use siphash. Old journal files use the Jenkins hash. */
1323
1324        if (JOURNAL_HEADER_KEYED_HASH(f->header))
1325                return siphash24(data, sz, f->header->file_id.bytes);
1326
1327        return jenkins_hash64(data, sz);
1328}

1345int journal_file_find_data_object_with_hash(
1346                JournalFile *f,
1347                const void *data, uint64_t size, uint64_t hash,
1348                Object **ret, uint64_t *ret_offset) {
1349
1350        uint64_t p, osize, h, m, depth = 0;
1351        int r;
1352
1353        assert(f);
1354        assert(f->header);
1355        assert(data || size == 0);
1356
1357        /* If there's no data hash table, then there's no entry. */
1358        if (le64toh(f->header->data_hash_table_size) <= 0)
1359                return 0;
1360
1361        /* Map the data hash table, if it isn't mapped yet. */
1362        r = journal_file_map_data_hash_table(f);
1363        if (r < 0)
1364                return r;
1365
1366        osize = offsetof(Object, data.payload) + size;
1367
1368        m = le64toh(READ_NOW(f->header->data_hash_table_size)) / sizeof(HashItem);
1369        if (m <= 0)
1370                return -EBADMSG;
1371
1372        h = hash % m;
1373        p = le64toh(f->data_hash_table[h].head_hash_offset);
1374
1375        while (p > 0) {
1376                Compression c;
1377                Object *o;
1378
1379                r = journal_file_move_to_object(f, OBJECT_DATA, p, &o);
1380                if (r < 0)
1381                        return r;
1382
1383                if (le64toh(o->data.hash) != hash)
1384                        goto next;
1385
1386                c = COMPRESSION_FROM_OBJECT(o);
1387                if (c < 0)
1388                        return -EPROTONOSUPPORT;
1389                if (c != COMPRESSION_NONE) {
1390#if HAVE_COMPRESSION
1391                        uint64_t l;
1392                        size_t rsize = 0;
1393
1394                        l = le64toh(READ_NOW(o->object.size));
1395                        if (l <= offsetof(Object, data.payload))
1396                                return -EBADMSG;
1397
1398                        l -= offsetof(Object, data.payload);
1399
1400                        r = decompress_blob(c, o->data.payload, l, &f->compress_buffer, &rsize, 0);
1401                        if (r < 0)
1402                                return r;
1403
1404                        if (rsize == size &&
1405                            memcmp(f->compress_buffer, data, size) == 0) {
1406
1407                                if (ret)
1408                                        *ret = o;
1409
1410                                if (ret_offset)
1411                                        *ret_offset = p;
1412
1413                                return 1;
1414                        }
1415#else
1416                        return -EPROTONOSUPPORT;
1417#endif
1418                } else if (le64toh(o->object.size) == osize &&
1419                           memcmp(o->data.payload, data, size) == 0) {
1420
1421                        if (ret)
1422                                *ret = o;
1423
1424                        if (ret_offset)
1425                                *ret_offset = p;
1426
1427                        return 1;
1428                }
1429
1430        next:
1431                r = next_hash_offset(
1432                                f,
1433                                &p,
1434                                &o->data.next_hash_offset,
1435                                &depth,
1436                                JOURNAL_HEADER_CONTAINS(f->header, data_hash_chain_depth) ? &f->header->data_hash_chain_depth : NULL);
1437                if (r < 0)
1438                        return r;
1439        }
1440
1441        return 0;
1442}

1459bool journal_field_valid(const char *p, size_t l, bool allow_protected) {
1460        /* We kinda enforce POSIX syntax recommendations for
1461           environment variables here, but make a couple of additional
1462           requirements.
1463
1464           http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/basedefs/xbd_chap08.html */
1465
1466        if (l == SIZE_MAX)
1467                l = strlen(p);
1468
1469        /* No empty field names */
1470        if (l <= 0)
1471                return false;
1472
1473        /* Don't allow names longer than 64 chars */
1474        if (l > 64)
1475                return false;
1476
1477        /* Variables starting with an underscore are protected */
1478        if (!allow_protected && p[0] == '_')
1479                return false;
1480
1481        /* Don't allow digits as first character */
1482        if (ascii_isdigit(p[0]))
1483                return false;
1484
1485        /* Only allow A-Z0-9 and '_' */
1486        for (const char *a = p; a < p + l; a++)
1487                if ((*a < 'A' || *a > 'Z') &&
1488                    !ascii_isdigit(*a) &&
1489                    *a != '_')
1490                        return false;
1491
1492        return true;
1493}

1495static int journal_file_append_field(
1496                JournalFile *f,
1497                const void *field, uint64_t size,
1498                Object **ret, uint64_t *ret_offset) {
1499
1500        uint64_t hash, p;
1501        uint64_t osize;
1502        Object *o;
1503        int r;
1504
1505        assert(f);
1506        assert(field && size > 0);
1507
1508        if (!journal_field_valid(field, size, true))
1509                return -EBADMSG;
1510
1511        hash = journal_file_hash_data(f, field, size);
1512
1513        r = journal_file_find_field_object_with_hash(f, field, size, hash, ret, ret_offset);
1514        if (r < 0)
1515                return r;
1516        if (r > 0)
1517                return 0;
1518
1519        osize = offsetof(Object, field.payload) + size;
1520        r = journal_file_append_object(f, OBJECT_FIELD, osize, &o, &p);
1521        if (r < 0)
1522                return r;
1523
1524        o->field.hash = htole64(hash);
1525        memcpy(o->field.payload, field, size);
1526
1527        r = journal_file_link_field(f, o, p, hash);
1528        if (r < 0)
1529                return r;
1530
1531        /* The linking might have altered the window, so let's only pass the offset to hmac which will
1532         * move to the object again if needed. */
1533
1534#if HAVE_GCRYPT
1535        r = journal_file_hmac_put_object(f, OBJECT_FIELD, NULL, p);
1536        if (r < 0)
1537                return r;
1538#endif
1539
1540        if (ret) {
1541                r = journal_file_move_to_object(f, OBJECT_FIELD, p, ret);
1542                if (r < 0)
1543                        return r;
1544        }
1545
1546        if (ret_offset)
1547                *ret_offset = p;
1548
1549        return 0;
1550}

1552static int journal_file_append_data(
1553                JournalFile *f,
1554                const void *data, uint64_t size,
1555                Object **ret, uint64_t *ret_offset) {
1556
1557        uint64_t hash, p, fp, osize;
1558        Object *o, *fo;
1559        int r, compression = 0;
1560        const void *eq;
1561
1562        assert(f);
1563
1564        if (!data || size == 0)
1565                return -EINVAL;
1566
1567        hash = journal_file_hash_data(f, data, size);
1568
1569        r = journal_file_find_data_object_with_hash(f, data, size, hash, ret, ret_offset);
1570        if (r < 0)
1571                return r;
1572        if (r > 0)
1573                return 0;
1574
1575        eq = memchr(data, '=', size);
1576        if (!eq)
1577                return -EINVAL;
1578
1579        osize = offsetof(Object, data.payload) + size;
1580        r = journal_file_append_object(f, OBJECT_DATA, osize, &o, &p);
1581        if (r < 0)
1582                return r;
1583
1584        o->data.hash = htole64(hash);
1585
1586#if HAVE_COMPRESSION
1587        if (JOURNAL_FILE_COMPRESS(f) && size >= f->compress_threshold_bytes) {
1588                size_t rsize = 0;
1589
1590                compression = compress_blob(data, size, o->data.payload, size - 1, &rsize);
1591                if (compression > COMPRESSION_NONE) {
1592                        o->object.size = htole64(offsetof(Object, data.payload) + rsize);
1593                        o->object.flags |= COMPRESSION_TO_OBJECT_FLAG(compression);
1594
1595                        log_debug("Compressed data object %"PRIu64" -> %zu using %s",
1596                                  size, rsize, compression_to_string(compression));
1597                } else
1598                        /* Compression didn't work, we don't really care why, let's continue without compression */
1599                        compression = COMPRESSION_NONE;
1600        }
1601#endif
1602
1603        if (compression == 0)
1604                memcpy_safe(o->data.payload, data, size);
1605
1606        r = journal_file_link_data(f, o, p, hash);
1607        if (r < 0)
1608                return r;
1609
1610        /* The linking might have altered the window, so let's refresh our pointer. */
1611        r = journal_file_move_to_object(f, OBJECT_DATA, p, &o);
1612        if (r < 0)
1613                return r;
1614
1615#if HAVE_GCRYPT
1616        r = journal_file_hmac_put_object(f, OBJECT_DATA, o, p);
1617        if (r < 0)
1618                return r;
1619#endif
1620
1621        /* Create field object ... */
1622        r = journal_file_append_field(f, data, (uint8_t*) eq - (uint8_t*) data, &fo, &fp);
1623        if (r < 0)
1624                return r;
1625
1626        /* ... and link it in. */
1627        o->data.next_field_offset = fo->field.head_data_offset;
1628        fo->field.head_data_offset = le64toh(p);
1629
1630        if (ret)
1631                *ret = o;
1632
1633        if (ret_offset)
1634                *ret_offset = p;
1635
1636        return 0;
1637}

1683static int link_entry_into_array(JournalFile *f,
1684                                 le64_t *first,
1685                                 le64_t *idx,
1686                                 uint64_t p) {
1687        int r;
1688        uint64_t n = 0, ap = 0, q, i, a, hidx;
1689        Object *o;
1690
1691        assert(f);
1692        assert(f->header);
1693        assert(first);
1694        assert(idx);
1695        assert(p > 0);
1696
1697        a = le64toh(*first);
1698        i = hidx = le64toh(READ_NOW(*idx));
1699        while (a > 0) {
1700
1701                r = journal_file_move_to_object(f, OBJECT_ENTRY_ARRAY, a, &o);
1702                if (r < 0)
1703                        return r;
1704
1705                n = journal_file_entry_array_n_items(o);
1706                if (i < n) {
1707                        o->entry_array.items[i] = htole64(p);
1708                        *idx = htole64(hidx + 1);
1709                        return 0;
1710                }
1711
1712                i -= n;
1713                ap = a;
1714                a = le64toh(o->entry_array.next_entry_array_offset);
1715        }
1716
1717        if (hidx > n)
1718                n = (hidx+1) * 2;
1719        else
1720                n = n * 2;
1721
1722        if (n < 4)
1723                n = 4;
1724
1725        r = journal_file_append_object(f, OBJECT_ENTRY_ARRAY,
1726                                       offsetof(Object, entry_array.items) + n * sizeof(uint64_t),
1727                                       &o, &q);
1728        if (r < 0)
1729                return r;
1730
1731#if HAVE_GCRYPT
1732        r = journal_file_hmac_put_object(f, OBJECT_ENTRY_ARRAY, o, q);
1733        if (r < 0)
1734                return r;
1735#endif
1736
1737        o->entry_array.items[i] = htole64(p);
1738
1739        if (ap == 0)
1740                *first = htole64(q);
1741        else {
1742                r = journal_file_move_to_object(f, OBJECT_ENTRY_ARRAY, ap, &o);
1743                if (r < 0)
1744                        return r;
1745
1746                o->entry_array.next_entry_array_offset = htole64(q);
1747        }
1748
1749        if (JOURNAL_HEADER_CONTAINS(f->header, n_entry_arrays))
1750                f->header->n_entry_arrays = htole64(le64toh(f->header->n_entry_arrays) + 1);
1751
1752        *idx = htole64(hidx + 1);
1753
1754        return 0;
1755}

1757static int link_entry_into_array_plus_one(JournalFile *f,
1758                                          le64_t *extra,
1759                                          le64_t *first,
1760                                          le64_t *idx,
1761                                          uint64_t p) {
1762
1763        uint64_t hidx;
1764        int r;
1765
1766        assert(f);
1767        assert(extra);
1768        assert(first);
1769        assert(idx);
1770        assert(p > 0);
1771
1772        hidx = le64toh(READ_NOW(*idx));
1773        if (hidx == UINT64_MAX)
1774                return -EBADMSG;

1783                        return r;

1785
1786        *idx = htole64(hidx + 1);
1787        return 0;

1795        assert(o);
1796        assert(offset > 0);

1799        r = journal_file_move_to_object(f, OBJECT_DATA, p, &o);

1810static int journal_file_link_entry(JournalFile *f, Object *o, uint64_t offset) {
1811        uint64_t n;
1812        int r;
1813
1814        assert(f);
1815        assert(f->header);
1816        assert(o);
1817        assert(offset > 0);
1818
1819        if (o->object.type != OBJECT_ENTRY)
1820                return -EINVAL;
1821
1822        __atomic_thread_fence(__ATOMIC_SEQ_CST);
1823
1824        /* Link up the entry itself */
1825        r = link_entry_into_array(f,
1826                                  &f->header->entry_array_offset,
1827                                  &f->header->n_entries,
1828                                  offset);
1829        if (r < 0)
1830                return r;
1831
1832        /* log_debug("=> %s seqnr=%"PRIu64" n_entries=%"PRIu64, f->path, o->entry.seqnum, f->header->n_entries); */
1833
1834        if (f->header->head_entry_realtime == 0)
1835                f->header->head_entry_realtime = o->entry.realtime;
1836
1837        f->header->tail_entry_realtime = o->entry.realtime;
1838        f->header->tail_entry_monotonic = o->entry.monotonic;
1839
1840        /* Link up the items */
1841        n = journal_file_entry_n_items(o);
1842        for (uint64_t i = 0; i < n; i++) {
1843                int k;
1844
1845                /* If we fail to link an entry item because we can't allocate a new entry array, don't fail
1846                 * immediately but try to link the other entry items since it might still be possible to link
1847                 * those if they don't require a new entry array to be allocated. */
1848
1849                k = journal_file_link_entry_item(f, o, offset, i);
1850                if (k == -E2BIG)
1851                        r = k;
1852                else if (k < 0)
1853                        return k;
1854        }
1855
1856        return r;
1857}

1859static int journal_file_append_entry_internal(
1860                JournalFile *f,
1861                const dual_timestamp *ts,

1863                uint64_t xor_hash,

1900                return r;

1911void journal_file_post_change(JournalFile *f) {
1912        assert(f);
1913
1914        if (f->fd < 0)
1915                return;
1916
1917        /* inotify() does not receive IN_MODIFY events from file
1918         * accesses done via mmap(). After each access we hence
1919         * trigger IN_MODIFY by truncating the journal file to its
1920         * current size which triggers IN_MODIFY. */
1921
1922        __atomic_thread_fence(__ATOMIC_SEQ_CST);
1923
1924        if (ftruncate(f->fd, f->last_stat.st_size) < 0)
1925                log_debug_errno(errno, "Failed to truncate file to its own size: %m");
1926}
1927
1928static int post_change_thunk(sd_event_source *timer, uint64_t usec, void *userdata) {
1929        assert(userdata);
1930
1931        journal_file_post_change(userdata);
1932
1933        return 1;
1934}

1936static void schedule_post_change(JournalFile *f) {
1937        sd_event *e;
1938        int r;
1939
1940        assert(f);
1941        assert(f->post_change_timer);
1942
1943        assert_se(e = sd_event_source_get_event(f->post_change_timer));
1944
1945        /* If we are already going down, post the change immediately. */
1946        if (IN_SET(sd_event_get_state(e), SD_EVENT_EXITING, SD_EVENT_FINISHED))
1947                goto fail;
1948
1949        r = sd_event_source_get_enabled(f->post_change_timer, NULL);
1950        if (r < 0) {
1951                log_debug_errno(r, "Failed to get ftruncate timer state: %m");
1952                goto fail;
1953        }
1954        if (r > 0)
1955                return;
1956
1957        r = sd_event_source_set_time_relative(f->post_change_timer, f->post_change_timer_period);
1958        if (r < 0) {
1959                log_debug_errno(r, "Failed to set time for scheduling ftruncate: %m");
1960                goto fail;
1961        }
1962
1963        r = sd_event_source_set_enabled(f->post_change_timer, SD_EVENT_ONESHOT);
1964        if (r < 0) {
1965                log_debug_errno(r, "Failed to enable scheduled ftruncate: %m");
1966                goto fail;
1967        }
1968
1969        return;
1970
1971fail:
1972        /* On failure, let's simply post the change immediately. */
1973        journal_file_post_change(f);
1974}
1975
1976/* Enable coalesced change posting in a timer on the provided sd_event instance */
1977int journal_file_enable_post_change_timer(JournalFile *f, sd_event *e, usec_t t) {
1978        _cleanup_(sd_event_source_unrefp) sd_event_source *timer = NULL;
1979        int r;
1980
1981        assert(f);
1982        assert_return(!f->post_change_timer, -EINVAL);
1983        assert(e);
1984        assert(t);
1985
1986        r = sd_event_add_time(e, &timer, CLOCK_MONOTONIC, 0, 0, post_change_thunk, f);
1987        if (r < 0)
1988                return r;
1989
1990        r = sd_event_source_set_enabled(timer, SD_EVENT_OFF);
1991        if (r < 0)
1992                return r;
1993
1994        f->post_change_timer = TAKE_PTR(timer);
1995        f->post_change_timer_period = t;
1996
1997        return r;
1998}

2004static size_t remove_duplicate_entry_items(EntryItem items[], size_t n) {
2005

2580static int generic_array_bisect_plus_one(
2581                JournalFile *f,
2582                uint64_t extra,
2583                uint64_t first,
2584                uint64_t n,
2585                uint64_t needle,
2586                int (*test_object)(JournalFile *f, uint64_t p, uint64_t needle),
2587                direction_t direction,
2588                Object **ret,
2589                uint64_t *ret_offset,
2590                uint64_t *ret_idx) {
2591
2592        int r;
2593        bool step_back = false;
2594
2595        assert(f);
2596        assert(test_object);
2597
2598        if (n <= 0)
2599                return 0;
2600
2601        /* This bisects the array in object 'first', but first checks
2602         * an extra  */
2603        r = test_object(f, extra, needle);
2604        if (r < 0)
2605                return r;
2606
2607        if (r == TEST_FOUND)
2608                r = direction == DIRECTION_DOWN ? TEST_RIGHT : TEST_LEFT;
2609
2610        /* if we are looking with DIRECTION_UP then we need to first
2611           see if in the actual array there is a matching entry, and
2612           return the last one of that. But if there isn't any we need
2613           to return this one. Hence remember this, and return it
2614           below. */
2615        if (r == TEST_LEFT)
2616                step_back = direction == DIRECTION_UP;
2617
2618        if (r == TEST_RIGHT) {
2619                if (direction == DIRECTION_DOWN)
2620                        goto found;
2621                else
2622                        return 0;
2623        }
2624
2625        r = generic_array_bisect(f, first, n-1, needle, test_object, direction, ret, ret_offset, ret_idx);
2626
2627        if (r == 0 && step_back)
2628                goto found;
2629

2631                (*ret_idx)++;
2632
2633        return r;
2634
2635found:
2636        if (ret) {
2637                r = journal_file_move_to_object(f, OBJECT_ENTRY, extra, ret);
2638                if (r < 0)
2639                        return r;
2640        }
2641
2642        if (ret_offset)
2643                *ret_offset = extra;
2644

2646                *ret_idx = 0;
2647
2648        return 1;

2896static bool check_properly_ordered(uint64_t new_offset, uint64_t old_offset, direction_t direction) {
2897
2898        /* Consider it an error if any of the two offsets is uninitialized */
2899        if (old_offset == 0 || new_offset == 0)
2900                return false;
2901
2902        /* If we go down, the new offset must be larger than the old one. */
2903        return direction == DIRECTION_DOWN ?
2904                new_offset > old_offset  :
2905                new_offset < old_offset;
2906}

3304static int journal_file_warn_btrfs(JournalFile *f) {
3305        unsigned attrs;
3306        int r;
3307
3308        assert(f);
3309
3310        /* Before we write anything, check if the COW logic is turned
3311         * off on btrfs. Given our write pattern that is quite
3312         * unfriendly to COW file systems this should greatly improve
3313         * performance on COW file systems, such as btrfs, at the
3314         * expense of data integrity features (which shouldn't be too
3315         * bad, given that we do our own checksumming). */
3316
3317        r = fd_is_fs_type(f->fd, BTRFS_SUPER_MAGIC);
3318        if (r < 0)
3319                return log_warning_errno(r, "Failed to determine if journal is on btrfs: %m");
3320        if (!r)
3321                return 0;
3322
3323        r = read_attr_fd(f->fd, &attrs);
3324        if (r < 0)
3325                return log_warning_errno(r, "Failed to read file attributes: %m");
3326
3327        if (attrs & FS_NOCOW_FL) {
3328                log_debug("Detected btrfs file system with copy-on-write disabled, all is good.");
3329                return 0;
3330        }
3331
3332        log_notice("Creating journal file %s on a btrfs file system, and copy-on-write is enabled. "
3333                   "This is likely to slow down journal access substantially, please consider turning "
3334                   "off the copy-on-write file attribute on the journal directory, using chattr +C.", f->path);
3335
3336        return 1;
3337}

3339static void journal_default_metrics(JournalMetrics *m, int fd) {
3340        struct statvfs ss;
3341        uint64_t fs_size = 0;
3342
3343        assert(m);
3344        assert(fd >= 0);
3345
3346        if (fstatvfs(fd, &ss) >= 0)
3347                fs_size = ss.f_frsize * ss.f_blocks;
3348        else
3349                log_debug_errno(errno, "Failed to determine disk size: %m");
3350
3351        if (m->max_use == UINT64_MAX) {
3352
3353                if (fs_size > 0)
3354                        m->max_use = CLAMP(PAGE_ALIGN(fs_size / 10), /* 10% of file system size */
3355                                           MAX_USE_LOWER, MAX_USE_UPPER);
3356                else
3357                        m->max_use = MAX_USE_LOWER;
3358        } else {
3359                m->max_use = PAGE_ALIGN(m->max_use);
3360
3361                if (m->max_use != 0 && m->max_use < JOURNAL_FILE_SIZE_MIN*2)
3362                        m->max_use = JOURNAL_FILE_SIZE_MIN*2;
3363        }
3364
3365        if (m->min_use == UINT64_MAX) {
3366                if (fs_size > 0)
3367                        m->min_use = CLAMP(PAGE_ALIGN(fs_size / 50), /* 2% of file system size */
3368                                           MIN_USE_LOW, MIN_USE_HIGH);
3369                else
3370                        m->min_use = MIN_USE_LOW;
3371        }
3372
3373        if (m->min_use > m->max_use)
3374                m->min_use = m->max_use;
3375
3376        if (m->max_size == UINT64_MAX)
3377                m->max_size = MIN(PAGE_ALIGN(m->max_use / 8), /* 8 chunks */
3378                                  MAX_SIZE_UPPER);
3379        else
3380                m->max_size = PAGE_ALIGN(m->max_size);
3381
3382        if (m->max_size != 0) {
3383                if (m->max_size < JOURNAL_FILE_SIZE_MIN)
3384                        m->max_size = JOURNAL_FILE_SIZE_MIN;
3385
3386                if (m->max_use != 0 && m->max_size*2 > m->max_use)
3387                        m->max_use = m->max_size*2;
3388        }
3389
3390        if (m->min_size == UINT64_MAX)
3391                m->min_size = JOURNAL_FILE_SIZE_MIN;
3392        else
3393                m->min_size = CLAMP(PAGE_ALIGN(m->min_size),
3394                                    JOURNAL_FILE_SIZE_MIN,
3395                                    m->max_size ?: UINT64_MAX);
3396
3397        if (m->keep_free == UINT64_MAX) {
3398                if (fs_size > 0)
3399                        m->keep_free = MIN(PAGE_ALIGN(fs_size / 20), /* 5% of file system size */
3400                                           KEEP_FREE_UPPER);
3401                else
3402                        m->keep_free = DEFAULT_KEEP_FREE;
3403        }
3404
3405        if (m->n_max_files == UINT64_MAX)
3406                m->n_max_files = DEFAULT_N_MAX_FILES;
3407
3408        log_debug("Fixed min_use=%s max_use=%s max_size=%s min_size=%s keep_free=%s n_max_files=%" PRIu64,
3409                  FORMAT_BYTES(m->min_use),
3410                  FORMAT_BYTES(m->max_use),
3411                  FORMAT_BYTES(m->max_size),
3412                  FORMAT_BYTES(m->min_size),
3413                  FORMAT_BYTES(m->keep_free),
3414                  m->n_max_files);
3415}

3435        assert(fd >= 0 || fname);
3436        assert(mmap_cache);
3437
3438        if (!IN_SET((open_flags & O_ACCMODE), O_RDONLY, O_RDWR))
3439                return -EINVAL;
3440

3442                return -EINVAL;
3443
3444        if (fname && (open_flags & O_CREAT) && !endswith(fname, ".journal"))
3445                return -EINVAL;
3446
3447        f = new(JournalFile, 1);
3448        if (!f)
3449                return -ENOMEM;
3450
3451        *f = (JournalFile) {
3452                .fd = fd,
3453                .mode = mode,
3454                .open_flags = open_flags,
3455                .compress_threshold_bytes = compress_threshold_bytes == UINT64_MAX ?
3456                                            DEFAULT_COMPRESS_THRESHOLD :
3457                                            MAX(MIN_COMPRESS_THRESHOLD, compress_threshold_bytes),
3458        };
3459
3460        if (fname) {
3461                f->path = strdup(fname);
3462                if (!f->path) {
3463                        r = -ENOMEM;
3464                        goto fail;
3465                }
3466        } else {
3467                assert(fd >= 0);
3468
3469                /* If we don't know the path, fill in something explanatory and vaguely useful */
3470                if (asprintf(&f->path, "/proc/self/%i", fd) < 0) {
3471                        r = -ENOMEM;
3472                        goto fail;
3473                }
3474        }
3475
3476        f->chain_cache = ordered_hashmap_new(&uint64_hash_ops);
3477        if (!f->chain_cache) {
3478                r = -ENOMEM;
3479                goto fail;
3480        }
3481
3482        if (f->fd < 0) {

3484                 * or so, we likely fail quickly than block for long. For regular files O_NONBLOCK has no effect, hence
3485                 * it doesn't hurt in that case. */

3487                f->fd = openat_report_new(AT_FDCWD, f->path, f->open_flags|O_CLOEXEC|O_NONBLOCK, f->mode, &newly_created);
3488                if (f->fd < 0) {
3489                        r = f->fd;
3490                        goto fail;
3491                }
3492
3493                /* fds we opened here by us should also be closed by us. */
3494                f->close_fd = true;
3495
3496                r = fd_nonblock(f->fd, false);
3497                if (r < 0)
3498                        goto fail;
3499
3500                if (!newly_created) {
3501                        r = journal_file_fstat(f);
3502                        if (r < 0)
3503                                goto fail;
3504                }
3505        } else {
3506                r = journal_file_fstat(f);
3507                if (r < 0)
3508                        goto fail;
3509
3510                /* If we just got the fd passed in, we don't really know if we created the file anew */
3511                newly_created = f->last_stat.st_size == 0 && journal_file_writable(f);
3512        }
3513
3514        f->cache_fd = mmap_cache_add_fd(mmap_cache, f->fd, prot_from_flags(open_flags));
3515        if (!f->cache_fd) {
3516                r = -ENOMEM;
3517                goto fail;
3518        }
3519
3520        if (newly_created) {
3521                (void) journal_file_warn_btrfs(f);
3522
3523                /* Let's attach the creation time to the journal file, so that the vacuuming code knows the age of this
3524                 * file even if the file might end up corrupted one day... Ideally we'd just use the creation time many
3525                 * file systems maintain for each file, but the API to query this is very new, hence let's emulate this
3526                 * via extended attributes. If extended attributes are not supported we'll just skip this, and rely
3527                 * solely on mtime/atime/ctime of the file. */
3528                (void) fd_setcrtime(f->fd, 0);
3529
3530                r = journal_file_init_header(f, file_flags, template);
3531                if (r < 0)
3532                        goto fail;
3533
3534                r = journal_file_fstat(f);
3535                if (r < 0)
3536                        goto fail;
3537        }
3538
3539        if (f->last_stat.st_size < (off_t) HEADER_SIZE_MIN) {
3540                r = -ENODATA;
3541                goto fail;
3542        }
3543
3544        r = mmap_cache_fd_get(f->cache_fd, CONTEXT_HEADER, true, 0, PAGE_ALIGN(sizeof(Header)), &f->last_stat, &h);
3545        if (r == -EINVAL) {
3546                /* Some file systems (jffs2 or p9fs) don't support mmap() properly (or only read-only
3547                 * mmap()), and return EINVAL in that case. Let's propagate that as a more recognizable error
3548                 * code. */
3549                r = -EAFNOSUPPORT;
3550                goto fail;
3551        }
3552        if (r < 0)
3553                goto fail;
3554
3555        f->header = h;
3556
3557        if (!newly_created) {
3558                r = journal_file_verify_header(f);
3559                if (r < 0)
3560                        goto fail;
3561        }
3562
3563#if HAVE_GCRYPT
3564        if (!newly_created && journal_file_writable(f) && JOURNAL_HEADER_SEALED(f->header)) {
3565                r = journal_file_fss_load(f);
3566                if (r < 0)
3567                        goto fail;
3568        }
3569#endif
3570
3571        if (journal_file_writable(f)) {
3572                if (metrics) {
3573                        journal_default_metrics(metrics, f->fd);
3574                        f->metrics = *metrics;
3575                } else if (template)
3576                        f->metrics = template->metrics;
3577
3578                r = journal_file_refresh_header(f);
3579                if (r < 0)
3580                        goto fail;
3581        }
3582
3583#if HAVE_GCRYPT
3584        r = journal_file_hmac_setup(f);
3585        if (r < 0)
3586                goto fail;
3587#endif
3588
3589        if (newly_created) {
3590                r = journal_file_setup_field_hash_table(f);
3591                if (r < 0)
3592                        goto fail;
3593
3594                r = journal_file_setup_data_hash_table(f);
3595                if (r < 0)
3596                        goto fail;
3597
3598#if HAVE_GCRYPT
3599                r = journal_file_append_first_tag(f);
3600                if (r < 0)
3601                        goto fail;
3602#endif
3603        }
3604
3605        if (mmap_cache_fd_got_sigbus(f->cache_fd)) {
3606                r = -EIO;
3607                goto fail;
3608        }
3609
3610        if (template && template->post_change_timer) {
3611                r = journal_file_enable_post_change_timer(
3612                                f,
3613                                sd_event_source_get_event(template->post_change_timer),
3614                                template->post_change_timer_period);
3615
3616                if (r < 0)
3617                        goto fail;
3618        }
3619
3620        /* The file is opened now successfully, thus we take possession of any passed in fd. */
3621        f->close_fd = true;
3622
3623        if (DEBUG_LOGGING) {
3624                static int last_seal = -1, last_compress = -1, last_keyed_hash = -1;
3625                static uint64_t last_bytes = UINT64_MAX;
3626
3627                if (last_seal != JOURNAL_HEADER_SEALED(f->header) ||
3628                    last_keyed_hash != JOURNAL_HEADER_KEYED_HASH(f->header) ||

3630                    last_bytes != f->compress_threshold_bytes) {
3631
3632                        log_debug("Journal effective settings seal=%s keyed_hash=%s compress=%s compress_threshold_bytes=%s",
3633                                  yes_no(JOURNAL_HEADER_SEALED(f->header)), yes_no(JOURNAL_HEADER_KEYED_HASH(f->header)),
3634                                  yes_no(JOURNAL_FILE_COMPRESS(f)), FORMAT_BYTES(f->compress_threshold_bytes));
3635                        last_seal = JOURNAL_HEADER_SEALED(f->header);
3636                        last_keyed_hash = JOURNAL_HEADER_KEYED_HASH(f->header);
3637                        last_compress = JOURNAL_FILE_COMPRESS(f);
3638                        last_bytes = f->compress_threshold_bytes;
3639                }
3640        }
3641
3642        *ret = f;
3643        return 0;
3644
3645fail:
3646        if (f->cache_fd && mmap_cache_fd_got_sigbus(f->cache_fd))
3647                r = -EIO;
3648
3649        (void) journal_file_close(f);
3650
3651        if (newly_created && fd < 0)
3652                (void) unlink(fname);
3653
3654        return r;
3655}
