3657int journal_file_archive(JournalFile *f, char **ret_previous_path) {
3658        _cleanup_free_ char *p = NULL;
3659
3660        assert(f);
3661
3662        if (!journal_file_writable(f))
3663                return -EINVAL;
3664
3665        /* Is this a journal file that was passed to us as fd? If so, we synthesized a path name for it, and we refuse
3666         * rotation, since we don't know the actual path, and couldn't rename the file hence. */
3667        if (path_startswith(f->path, "/proc/self/fd"))
3668                return -EINVAL;
3669
3670        if (!endswith(f->path, ".journal"))
3671                return -EINVAL;
3672
3673        if (asprintf(&p, "%.*s@" SD_ID128_FORMAT_STR "-%016"PRIx64"-%016"PRIx64".journal",
3674                     (int) strlen(f->path) - 8, f->path,
3675                     SD_ID128_FORMAT_VAL(f->header->seqnum_id),
3676                     le64toh(f->header->head_entry_seqnum),
3677                     le64toh(f->header->head_entry_realtime)) < 0)
3678                return -ENOMEM;
3679
3680        /* Try to rename the file to the archived version. If the file already was deleted, we'll get ENOENT, let's
3681         * ignore that case. */
3682        if (rename(f->path, p) < 0 && errno != ENOENT)
3683                return -errno;
3684
3685        /* Sync the rename to disk */
3686        (void) fsync_directory_of_file(f->fd);
3687
3688        if (ret_previous_path)
3689                *ret_previous_path = f->path;
3690        else
3691                free(f->path);
3692
3693        f->path = TAKE_PTR(p);
3694
3695        /* Set as archive so offlining commits w/state=STATE_ARCHIVED. Previously we would set old_file->header->state
3696         * to STATE_ARCHIVED directly here, but journal_file_set_offline() short-circuits when state != STATE_ONLINE,
3697         * which would result in the rotated journal never getting fsync() called before closing.  Now we simply queue
3698         * the archive state by setting an archive bit, leaving the state as STATE_ONLINE so proper offlining
3699         * occurs. */
3700        f->archive = true;
3701
3702        return 0;
3703}

3705int journal_file_dispose(int dir_fd, const char *fname) {
3706        _cleanup_free_ char *p = NULL;
3707
3708        assert(fname);
3709
3710        /* Renames a journal file to *.journal~, i.e. to mark it as corrupted or otherwise uncleanly shutdown. Note that
3711         * this is done without looking into the file or changing any of its contents. The idea is that this is called
3712         * whenever something is suspicious and we want to move the file away and make clear that it is not accessed
3713         * for writing anymore. */
3714
3715        if (!endswith(fname, ".journal"))
3716                return -EINVAL;
3717
3718        if (asprintf(&p, "%.*s@%016" PRIx64 "-%016" PRIx64 ".journal~",
3719                     (int) strlen(fname) - 8, fname,
3720                     now(CLOCK_REALTIME),
3721                     random_u64()) < 0)
3722                return -ENOMEM;
3723
3724        if (renameat(dir_fd, fname, dir_fd, p) < 0)
3725                return -errno;
3726
3727        return 0;
3728}

3730int journal_file_copy_entry(JournalFile *from, JournalFile *to, Object *o, uint64_t p) {
3731        uint64_t q, n, xor_hash = 0;
3732        const sd_id128_t *boot_id;
3733        dual_timestamp ts;
3734        EntryItem *items;
3735        int r;
3736
3737        assert(from);
3738        assert(to);
3739        assert(o);
3740        assert(p);
3741
3742        if (!journal_file_writable(to))
3743                return -EPERM;
3744
3745        ts = (dual_timestamp) {
3746                .monotonic = le64toh(o->entry.monotonic),
3747                .realtime = le64toh(o->entry.realtime),
3748        };
3749        boot_id = &o->entry.boot_id;
3750
3751        n = journal_file_entry_n_items(o);
3752        items = newa(EntryItem, n);
3753
3754        for (uint64_t i = 0; i < n; i++) {
3755                Compression c;
3756                uint64_t l, h;
3757                size_t t;
3758                void *data;
3759                Object *u;
3760
3761                q = le64toh(o->entry.items[i].object_offset);
3762
3763                r = journal_file_move_to_object(from, OBJECT_DATA, q, &o);
3764                if (r < 0)
3765                        return r;
3766
3767                l = le64toh(READ_NOW(o->object.size));
3768                if (l < offsetof(Object, data.payload))
3769                        return -EBADMSG;
3770
3771                l -= offsetof(Object, data.payload);
3772                t = (size_t) l;
3773
3774                /* We hit the limit on 32bit machines */
3775                if ((uint64_t) t != l)
3776                        return -E2BIG;
3777
3778                c = COMPRESSION_FROM_OBJECT(o);
3779                if (c < 0)
3780                        return -EPROTONOSUPPORT;
3781                if (c != COMPRESSION_NONE) {
3782#if HAVE_COMPRESSION
3783                        size_t rsize = 0;
3784
3785                        r = decompress_blob(
3786                                        c,
3787                                        o->data.payload, l,
3788                                        &from->compress_buffer, &rsize,
3789                                        0);
3790                        if (r < 0)
3791                                return r;
3792
3793                        data = from->compress_buffer;
3794                        l = rsize;
3795#else
3796                        return -EPROTONOSUPPORT;
3797#endif
3798                } else
3799                        data = o->data.payload;
3800
3801                if (l == 0)
3802                        return -EBADMSG;
3803
3804                r = journal_file_append_data(to, data, l, &u, &h);
3805                if (r < 0)
3806                        return r;
3807
3808                if (JOURNAL_HEADER_KEYED_HASH(to->header))
3809                        xor_hash ^= jenkins_hash64(data, l);
3810                else
3811                        xor_hash ^= le64toh(u->data.hash);
3812
3813                items[i] = (EntryItem) {
3814                        .object_offset = htole64(h),
3815                        .hash = u->data.hash,
3816                };
3817
3818                r = journal_file_move_to_object(from, OBJECT_ENTRY, p, &o);
3819                if (r < 0)
3820                        return r;
3821        }
3822
3823        r = journal_file_append_entry_internal(to, &ts, boot_id, xor_hash, items, n, NULL, NULL, NULL);
3824
3825        if (mmap_cache_fd_got_sigbus(to->cache_fd))
3826                return -EIO;
3827
3828        return r;
3829}

3911bool journal_file_rotate_suggested(JournalFile *f, usec_t max_file_usec, int log_level) {
3912        assert(f);
3913        assert(f->header);
3914
3915        /* If we gained new header fields we gained new features,
3916         * hence suggest a rotation */
3917        if (le64toh(f->header->header_size) < sizeof(Header)) {
3918                log_full(log_level, "%s uses an outdated header, suggesting rotation.", f->path);
3919                return true;
3920        }
3921
3922        /* Let's check if the hash tables grew over a certain fill level (75%, borrowing this value from
3923         * Java's hash table implementation), and if so suggest a rotation. To calculate the fill level we
3924         * need the n_data field, which only exists in newer versions. */
3925
3926        if (JOURNAL_HEADER_CONTAINS(f->header, n_data))
3927                if (le64toh(f->header->n_data) * 4ULL > (le64toh(f->header->data_hash_table_size) / sizeof(HashItem)) * 3ULL) {
3928                        log_full(log_level,
3929                                 "Data hash table of %s has a fill level at %.1f (%"PRIu64" of %"PRIu64" items, %llu file size, %"PRIu64" bytes per hash table item), suggesting rotation.",
3930                                 f->path,
3931                                 100.0 * (double) le64toh(f->header->n_data) / ((double) (le64toh(f->header->data_hash_table_size) / sizeof(HashItem))),
3932                                 le64toh(f->header->n_data),
3933                                 le64toh(f->header->data_hash_table_size) / sizeof(HashItem),
3934                                 (unsigned long long) f->last_stat.st_size,
3935                                 f->last_stat.st_size / le64toh(f->header->n_data));
3936                        return true;
3937                }
3938
3939        if (JOURNAL_HEADER_CONTAINS(f->header, n_fields))
3940                if (le64toh(f->header->n_fields) * 4ULL > (le64toh(f->header->field_hash_table_size) / sizeof(HashItem)) * 3ULL) {
3941                        log_full(log_level,
3942                                 "Field hash table of %s has a fill level at %.1f (%"PRIu64" of %"PRIu64" items), suggesting rotation.",
3943                                 f->path,
3944                                 100.0 * (double) le64toh(f->header->n_fields) / ((double) (le64toh(f->header->field_hash_table_size) / sizeof(HashItem))),
3945                                 le64toh(f->header->n_fields),
3946                                 le64toh(f->header->field_hash_table_size) / sizeof(HashItem));
3947                        return true;
3948                }
3949
3950        /* If there are too many hash collisions somebody is most likely playing games with us. Hence, if our
3951         * longest chain is longer than some threshold, let's suggest rotation. */
3952        if (JOURNAL_HEADER_CONTAINS(f->header, data_hash_chain_depth) &&
3953            le64toh(f->header->data_hash_chain_depth) > HASH_CHAIN_DEPTH_MAX) {
3954                log_full(log_level,
3955                         "Data hash table of %s has deepest hash chain of length %" PRIu64 ", suggesting rotation.",
3956                         f->path, le64toh(f->header->data_hash_chain_depth));
3957                return true;
3958        }
3959
3960        if (JOURNAL_HEADER_CONTAINS(f->header, field_hash_chain_depth) &&
3961            le64toh(f->header->field_hash_chain_depth) > HASH_CHAIN_DEPTH_MAX) {
3962                log_full(log_level,
3963                         "Field hash table of %s has deepest hash chain of length at %" PRIu64 ", suggesting rotation.",
3964                         f->path, le64toh(f->header->field_hash_chain_depth));
3965                return true;
3966        }
3967
3968        /* Are the data objects properly indexed by field objects? */
3969        if (JOURNAL_HEADER_CONTAINS(f->header, n_data) &&
3970            JOURNAL_HEADER_CONTAINS(f->header, n_fields) &&
3971            le64toh(f->header->n_data) > 0 &&
3972            le64toh(f->header->n_fields) == 0) {
3973                log_full(log_level,
3974                         "Data objects of %s are not indexed by field objects, suggesting rotation.",
3975                         f->path);
3976                return true;
3977        }
3978
3979        if (max_file_usec > 0) {
3980                usec_t t, h;
3981
3982                h = le64toh(f->header->head_entry_realtime);
3983                t = now(CLOCK_REALTIME);
3984
3985                if (h > 0 && t > h + max_file_usec) {
3986                        log_full(log_level,
3987                                 "Oldest entry in %s is older than the configured file retention duration (%s), suggesting rotation.",
3988                                 f->path, FORMAT_TIMESPAN(max_file_usec, USEC_PER_SEC));
3989                        return true;
3990                }
3991        }
3992
3993        return false;
3994}
3995
3996static const char * const journal_object_type_table[] = {
3997        [OBJECT_UNUSED] = "unused",
3998        [OBJECT_DATA] = "data",
3999        [OBJECT_FIELD] = "field",
4000        [OBJECT_ENTRY] = "entry",
4001        [OBJECT_DATA_HASH_TABLE] = "data hash table",
4002        [OBJECT_FIELD_HASH_TABLE] = "field hash table",
4003        [OBJECT_ENTRY_ARRAY] = "entry array",
4004        [OBJECT_TAG] = "tag",
4005};
4006
4007DEFINE_STRING_TABLE_LOOKUP_TO_STRING(journal_object_type, ObjectType);
